## 1. [Tags & Macros](#1-tags--macros)

#### 1.1. [Tags](#1-1-tags)

- Purpose: Tags are an essential Gravwell concept. Every entry has a single tag associated with it; these tags allow us to separate and categorize data at a basic level.
- [Documentation](https://docs.gravwell.io/ingesters/ingesters.html#tags)
- The Fortinet Kit for Gravwell makes use of the following tags:
    - fortinet: Tag contains all Fortinet data (all log types).
        - Usage: tag=fortinet-*
    - fortinet-system: Tag contains Fortinet System log data.
        - Usage: tag=fortinet-system
    - fortinet-events: Tag contains Fortinet Events log data.
        - Usage: tag=fortinet-events
    - fortinet-utm: Tag contains Fortinet UTM log data.
        - Usage: tag=fortinet-utm
    - fortinet-traffic: Tag contains Fortinet Traffic log data.
        - Usage: tag=fortinet-traffic

#### 1.2. [Autoextractors](#1-2-autoextractors)

- Purpose: Auto-extractors are simply definitions that can be applied to tags and describe how to correctly extract fields from the data in a given tag. The “ax” module then automatically invokes the appropriate functionality of other modules.
- [Documentation](https://docs.gravwell.io/configuration/autoextractors.html)
- The Fortinet Kit for Gravwell makes use of the following autoextractors:
    - fortinet-events
        - Auto-generated fields extraction for tag fortinet-events
    - fortinet-system
        - Auto-generated fields extraction for tag fortinet-system
    - fortinet-traffic
        - Auto-generated fields extraction for tag fortinet-traffic
    - fortinet-utm
        - Auto-generated fields extraction for tag fortinet-utm

#### 1.3. [Macros](#1-3-macros)

- Purpose: Search macros are a powerful feature that can help you use Gravwell more effectively. Macros can turn long, repetitive search queries into easily-remembered shortcuts.
- [Documentation](https://docs.gravwell.io/search/macros.html)
- The Fortinet Kit for Gravwell makes use of the following macros:
    - Tags
        - $FORTINET: Configuration Macro; Tag used for querying all Fortinet data; necessary for any queries within the Gravwell Fortinet Kit to run properly for dashboards, query library, and templates.
            - Usage: `tag=$FORTINET`
        - $FORTINET\_SYSTEM: Configuration Macro; Tag used for Fortinet System data; necessary for any queries within the Gravwell Fortinet Kit to run properly for dashboards, query library, and templates.
            - Usage: `tag=$FORTINET_SYSTEM`
        - $FORTINET\_EVENTS: Configuration Macro; Tag used for Fortinet Events data; necessary for any queries within the Gravwell Fortinet Kit to run properly for dashboards, query library, and templates.
            - Usage: `tag=$FORTINET_EVENTS`
        - $FORTINET\_UTM: Configuration Macro; Tag used for Fortinet UTM data; necessary for any queries within the Gravwell Fortinet Kit to run properly for dashboards, query library, and templates.
            - Usage: `tag=$FORTINET_UTM`
        - $FORTINET\_TRAFFIC: Configuration Macro; Tag used for Fortinet Traffic data; necessary for any queries within the Gravwell Fortinet Kit to run properly for dashboards, query library, and templates.
            - Usage: `tag=$FORTINET_TRAFFIC`
    - EVX (Enumerated Value Extraction)
        - $FORTINET\_EVX: This macro is intended to be used with $FORTINET as it extracts every possible Enumerated Value (EV) for any of the Fortinet logs.
            - Usage: `tag=$FORTINET $FORTINET_EVX`
    - Alert Components
    - Dashboard Components

