## 3. [Naming Schema](#3-naming-schema)

- Purpose: The use of a standard naming convention enables users to quickly understand the function, severity, and context of a query or component. This approach facilitates efficient identification, reuse, and troubleshooting without ambiguity.
- _QueryType - Company - Category/Logtype - Subcategory/Log Subtype - Severity/Priority - Name [Visualization - **if any**]_
- Examples:
    - Dashboards: _Dashboard - Fortinet - Traffic - Overview_
    - Templates: _Template - Fortinet - Traffic - EV - Count [chart]_

***

## 4. [Resources](#4-resources)
- Purpose: Resources allow users to store persistent data for use in searches.
- [Documentation](https://docs.gravwell.io/resources/resources.html)

#### 4.1 [Lookups](#4-1-lookups)
- Purpose: Lookup Resources are used by the lookup module to perform data enrichment and translation off of a static lookup table stored in a resource.
- [Documentation](https://docs.gravwell.io/search/lookup/lookup.html)
- Total: 7
    - fortinet\_evs  
        - This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet enumerated values (EVs). It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.  
        - Fields: ev, description, example  
            - ev: the Enumerated Value (EV) name/category to match upon  
            - description: additional information about the EV  
            - example: example value format  
        - Reference(s):  
            - [Fortinet Log Message Reference](https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.6/fortios-log-message-reference/357866)
        - Usage: `dump -r fortinet_evs | table`

    - fortinet\_protocol\_state  
        - This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet protocol states. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.  
        - Fields: state, description  
            - state: protocol state name for the event  
            - description: more information about the state  
        - Reference(s):  
            - [Fortinet Troubleshooting Tip](https://community.fortinet.com/t5/FortiGate/Troubleshooting-Tip-FortiGate-session-table-information/ta-p/196988)  
        - Usage: `dump -r fortinet_protocol_state | table`

    - fortinet\_log\_types  
        - This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet log types. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.  
        - Fields: category, subcategory, description  
            - category: log category for the event  
            - subcategory: log subcategory for the event  
            - description: more information about the subcategory  
        - Reference(s): [Fortinet Log Message Reference](https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/160372)          
        - Usage: `dump -r fortinet_log_types | table`

    - fortinet\_priority  
        - This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet priority levels. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.  
        - Fields: priority, name, description  
            - priority: priority level for the event  
            - name: priority name for the event  
            - description: more information about the priority  
        - Reference(s): [Fortinet Priority Levels](https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/446022/fortios-priority-levels)  
        - Usage: `dump -r fortinet_priority | table`

    - fortinet\_protocols  
        - This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet protocols. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.  
        - Fields: proto\_id, protocol, proto\_state, state, description, expiry\_timer  
            - proto\_id: protocol id for the event  
            - protocol: protocol name  
            - proto\_state: protocol state for the event  
            - state: protocol state name for the event  
            - description: more information about the protocol/state  
            - expiry\_timer: default expiry timer for that protocol and state  
        - Reference(s):  
            - [Fortinet Troubleshooting Tip](https://community.fortinet.com/t5/FortiGate/Troubleshooting-Tip-FortiGate-session-table-information/ta-p/196988)  
        - Usage: `dump -r fortinet_protocols | table`

    - fortinet\_log\_ids  
        - This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet log types and subtypes. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.  
        - Fields: category, category\_id, subcategory, subcategory\_id, name, description, risk\_score  
            - category: log category for the event  
            - category\_id: log category id for the event  
            - subcategory: log subcategory for the event  
            - subcategory\_id: log subcategory id for the event  
            - name: log subcategory name  
            - description: more information about the subcategory  
            - risk\_score: associated risk score for the log category/subcategory  
        - Reference(s):  
            - [Fortinet Log ID Numbers](https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/034314/log-id-numbers)  
            - [Fortinet Log ID Definitions](https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/656858/log-id-definitions)  
            - [Fortinet Log Message Reference](https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/160372)  
        
        - Usage: `dump -r fortinet_log_ids | table`

    - fortinet\_url\_category  
        - This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet url categories. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.  
        
        - Fields: category, category\_id, subcategory, subcategory\_id, description, risk\_score  
            - category: url category for the event  
            - category\_id: url category id for the event  
            - subcategory: log subcategory for the event  
            - subcategory\_id: log subcategory id for the event  
            - description: more information about the subcategory  
            - risk\_score: associated risk score for the url category/subcategory  
        - Reference(s):  
            - [Fortinet Troubleshooting Tip](https://community.fortinet.com/t5/FortiGate/Troubleshooting-Tip-FortiGate-session-table-information/ta-p/196988)  
        
        - Usage: `dump -r fortinet_url_category | table`

